  40.4.16 ESMF_InfoGetFromHost - Get an Info handle from an ESMF object

   INTERFACE:
  subroutine ESMF_InfoGetFromHost(host, info, rc)

   ARGUMENTS:
    type(ESMF_*), intent(inout) :: host
    type(ESMF_Info), intent(out) :: info
 -- The following arguments require argument keyword syntax (e.g. rc=rc). --
    integer, intent(out), optional :: rc

   DESCRIPTION:

   Get an ESMF_Info object handle from a host ESMF object. The returned
   handle should not be destroyed.

   The arguments are:

   host
          Target ESMF object. Overloaded for:

          + ESMF_Array
          + ESMF_ArrayBundle
          + ESMF_CplComp
          + ESMF_GridComp
          + ESMF_SciComp
          + ESMF_DistGrid
          + ESMF_Field
          + ESMF_FieldBundle
          + ESMF_Grid
          + ESMF_State
          + ESMF_LocStream
          + ESMF_Mesh

   info
          Outgoing ESMF_Info object.

   [rc]
          Return code; equals ESMF_SUCCESS if there are no errors.

